          <description>
            <string language="de-DE">It is a realistic assumption that in a united Europe some of our students will apply for a job in another country, where their working language is English. 

Moreover simulations are always attractive tasks which students fulfil with great interest and enthusiasm. Throughout the unit they will work with authentic material taken from the internet. 



TO START THE UNIT, PLEASE UNZIP THE FILE, KLICK ON THE 'INDEX'-DOCUMENT(HTML) AND FOLLOW THE ADVISORY: ALL OTHER DOCUMENTS ARE LINKED TO THE INDEX-FILE: HAVE FUN!



Outline : 

In order to get into the topic students will first acquire the necessary vocabulary. 

They will revise the new words and the tenses with further exercises. 

They will then study job advertisements and get a clearer idea of present dayrequirements for jobs they are interested in. 

Later they will draft their own CVs and letters of application. 

They will finally prepare for and act out a job interview. 



Objectives : 

Students should practice the 4 skills in language learning. 

READING : Studying the job advertisements. 

WRITING: Drafting CVs and letters of application. 

SPEAKING: Presenting your dream job and your candidate, discussing job advertisements, role playing the job interviews. 

LISTENING: Interactive websites.</string>
          </description>
